Subject: Re: [T2] Leisure battery and charging

On Jan 20, 2004, at 10:01 AM, Eric Ryplewski wrote:

> To answer your question:  An isolator prevents the aux battery from
> draining the starting battery.  A relay will not do this.  If you leave
> your key on with the engine not running the starting battery will 
> charge
> the aux battery on it's own until they reach equilibrium.

Only if you wire up the relay incorrectly.  I believe the stock wiring 
configuration is to use alternator output as the signal input to the 
relay, which means the relay would only close if the engine is running.

